text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia cockertoniana is a tree belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to the Mid West and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The tree typically grows to a height of 3 to 6 metres (10 to 20 ft) with rough grey bark on a deeply fissured trunk and stems becoming smooth on upper branches.
